      <p>You bought the monitor, the hub, the charging stand, the lamp, and the keyboard. Now your desk looks like a spaghetti factory. A cable management box hides the power strip and adapters in one enclosed unit, while adhesive clips route the last twelve inches of every wire along the back edge of your desk. We evaluated eight kits based on their specifications and design features to find which ones actually produce a clean surface versus just relocating the mess.</p>

      <h2 id="how-we-evaluated">How We Evaluated</h2>
      <p>We evaluated 8 cable management models based on product documentation, specifications, feature analysis, and pricing comparison. Our evaluation methodology follows the <a href="/how-we-test/">ToolStep review protocol</a>, analyzing product documentation, specifications, features, and pricing. Each product was assessed across identical criteria to ensure fair comparison.</p>
      <p>We evaluated each product on four criteria: Performance (30%), Build Quality (25%), Value (20%), and Ease of Use (25%). Scores were compiled from specification analysis and feature evaluation, not marketing claims. Each box was assessed for capacity based on internal dimensions and surge protector compatibility, and ventilation was evaluated based on vent design and heat dissipation features. Adhesive clips were assessed based on adhesive specifications and surface compatibility claims.</p>

      <h2 id="ranking-methodology">Ranking Methodology</h2>
      <p>Our rankings are based on weighted scoring across four dimensions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Performance (30%)</strong> — How well does the product contain and route cables?</li>
        <li><strong>Build Quality (25%)</strong> — Materials, ventilation, and lid durability</li>
        <li><strong>Value (20%)</strong> — Price-to-performance ratio compared to alternatives</li>
        <li><strong>Ease of Use (25%)</strong> — Installation, repositioning, and daily access to plugs</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="quick-comparison">Quick Comparison</h2>
      <table>
