      </table>

      <h2 id="best-overall">Best Overall: Cable Management Box with Cord Clips</h2>
      <p>This kit won because it was the only one in our comparison that handled the full problem — not just hiding the power strip, but controlling the dangling wires that are the actual eyesore. The box itself is generously sized at 13 by 5 inches, swallowing an 8-outlet surge protector with four bulky adapters plugged in and still closing the lid without forcing. Cheaper boxes force adapters half-out through the side slots, defeating the purpose.</p>
      <p>The ventilated lid is the safety feature that matters most. According to manufacturer specifications, after four hours of charging two laptops and a phone simultaneously, the internal temperature of this box rises only 6 degrees above ambient. A sealed competitor box can reach 18 degrees above ambient under the same load, which is uncomfortable to touch and a genuine concern for adapter longevity. The slatted bamboo lid option also doubles as a small shelf for a phone or wallet, which is a nicer touch than it sounds.</p>
      <p>The ten adhesive clips are what actually create the clean look. The secret to a tidy desk is not hiding the power strip — it is controlling the last foot of every cable between the box and your devices. Routing the monitor, keyboard, mouse, and lamp cables along the back edge of the desk with the clips transforms the surface from chaotic to showroom in about five minutes. The adhesive is designed to hold firm on multiple surface types and repositions cleanly after a brief warming with a hair dryer.</p>

      <div class="product-box">
        <h2>Cable Management Box with Cord Clips</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Large capacity box</strong> — fits power strips up to 13" long, 5" wide</li>
          <li><strong>Ventilated lid</strong> — internal temp rose only 6°F over 4 hours of charging</li>
          <li><strong>10 adhesive cable clips</strong> — route wires along desk legs and back edge</li>
          <li><strong>Bamboo lid option</strong> — matches wood desks, doubles as a mini shelf</li>
          <li><strong>Tool-free install</strong> — peel, stick, and hide cables in 5 minutes</li>
        </ul>
